## Strategic Benefits

### 1. Stream Whenever You Want
You love gaming. This lets you do it publicly, on your schedule, with no 24/7 pressure. That's the Inn's job.

### 2. Testing Ground
Every overlay, alert sound, emote, and channel point redemption—test it during E.I. Werner streams first. Work out the kinks before Outside Inn's full launch.

### 3. Content Engine
Streams generate clips. Clips feed X, Instagram, TikTok, YouTube Shorts. You're marketing Outside Inn before it even launches—just by being yourself.

### 4. Audience Funnel
People follow people, not projects. They discover E.I. Werner → watch the stream → get exposed to Outside Inn → become Innsiders. You're the front door.

### 5. The WoW Lore Series Is the Bridge
The Deadkeep series—uncovering the lost history of the Outside Inn through WoW's Archaeology profession—is E.I. Werner content that *literally* tells the Outside Inn origin story. Marketing disguised as gameplay.

### 6. Mixed Audiences Compound
Outside Inn radio viewers see you when you go live. Your gaming viewers get exposed to the Inn and Carson's music. Both audiences grow together.

